main event: A civilian reported witnessing an unidentified object in Kettering, Ohio on August 23, 1965, for a duration of 3 minutes.
interesting points: The object was visible for a total duration of 3 minutes,The source of the report is from a civilian witness,The course of the object was noted as moving northeast,The report concluded that the sighting was possibly a satellite,There were no photographs or physical evidence presented in the report.
witness description: a 12-year-old male with an interest in astronomy
